oltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00016"><b><p>The SPIDERFANG keyword is used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">None</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Spider-Riders" style="color:#101010">Spider Riders</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Scuttleboss-on-Gigantic-Spider" style="color:#101010">Scuttleboss on Gigantic Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Arachnarok-Spider-with-Flinger" style="color:#101010">Arachnarok Spider with Flinger</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Arachnarok-Spider-with-Spiderfang-Warparty" style="color:#101010">Arachnarok Spider with Spiderfang Warparty</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skitterstrand-Arachnarok" style="color:#101010">Skitterstrand Arachnarok</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00017"><b><p>The TROGGOTH keyword is used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">None</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Dankhold-Troggoths" style="color:#101010">Dankhold Troggoths</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Fellwater-Troggoths" style="color:#101010">Fellwater Troggoths</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Rockgut-Troggoths" style="color:#101010">Rockgut Troggoths</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Dankhold-Troggboss" style="color:#101010">Dankhold Troggboss</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Mollog" style="color:#101010">Mollog</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  class="clFl sForgeWorld" style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Forge World: Monstrous Arcanum (2th edition)" src="/aos/img/expansions/FW_AoS_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Troggoth-Hag" style="color:#101010">Troggoth Hag</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00018"><div class="tooltip_header">Healing Wounds</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Healing-Wounds"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Some abilities allow wounds that have been <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Allocating-Wounds">allocated</a> to a model to be healed. For each wound that is healed, remove one of the wounds that have been allocated to the model. You can’t heal wounds on a model that has been slain.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00019"><b><p>The LOONBOSS keyword is used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss" style="color:#101010">Loonboss</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Giant-Cave-Squig" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Giant Cave Squig</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-with-Giant-Cave-Squig" style="color:#101010">Loonboss with Giant Cave Squig</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skragrott-the-Loonking" style="color:#101010">Skragrott, the Loonking</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Mangler-Squigs" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Mangler Squigs</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00020"><div class="tooltip_header">Melee Weapons</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Melee-Weapons"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
In order to make an attack with a melee weapon, a model must be in range of the target unit.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00021"><b><p>The BAD MOON LOONSHRINE keyword is used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Scenery</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="White Dwarf’07/20 Jaws of Mork (2th edition)" src="/aos/img/expansions/WhiteDwarf_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Bad-Moon-Loonshrine" style="color:#101010">Bad Moon Loonshrine</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00022"><b><p>The MOONCLAN and <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WIZARDS">WIZARD</a> keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">None</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Boggleye" style="color:#101010">Boggleye</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Shroomancer" style="color:#101010">Shroomancer</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Fungoid-Cave-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Fungoid Cave-Shaman</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Madcap-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Madcap Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skragrott-the-Loonking" style="color:#101010">Skragrott, the Loonking</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Zarbag" style="color:#101010">Zarbag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00023"><b><p>The SCUTTLEBOSS keyword is used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Scuttleboss-on-Gigantic-Spider" style="color:#101010">Scuttleboss on Gigantic Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00024"><div class="tooltip_header">Cover</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Cover"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Add 1 to <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Making-Attacks">save rolls</a> for a unit if all of its models are wholly on or within a <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#TERRAIN">terrain</a> feature when the rolls are made. This modifier does not apply in the <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#COMBAT-PHASE">combat phase</a> if the unit you are making save rolls for made a <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#CHARGE-PHASE">charge move</a> in the same turn, and never applies to units containing models with the MONSTER or WAR MACHINE keyword that have a Wounds characteristic of 8 or more.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00025"><b><p>The DANKHOLD, TROGGOTH and HERO keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Dankhold-Troggboss" style="color:#101010">Dankhold Troggboss</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Mollog" style="color:#101010">Mollog</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00026"><b><p>The SPIDERFANG and HERO keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Scuttleboss-on-Gigantic-Spider" style="color:#101010">Scuttleboss on Gigantic Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00027"><div class="tooltip_header">Unbinding and Dispelling</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/conquest-unbound#Unbinding-and-Dispelling"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
A <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WIZARDS">WIZARD</a> can attempt to unbind an endless spell when it is initially cast as normal. In addition, a WIZARD can attempt to dispel one endless spell at the start of each of their <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#HERO-PHASE">hero phases</a>. If a wizard attempts to dispel an endless spell, they can attempt to cast one less spell than normal that phase.<br><br>In order to dispel an endless spell, first pick an endless spell model within 30" of the wizard and visible to them, and then roll 2D6. If the roll is greater than the <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Casting-Spells">casting value</a> of the spell, the endless spell is dispelled. An endless spell model cannot be subjected to more than one dispel attempt per hero phase.<br><br>When an endless spell is dispelled its model is removed from play; the model can then be used again if the same endless spell is successfully cast later in the battle.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00028"><div class="tooltip_header">Allocating Wounds</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Allocating-Wounds"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Once all of a unit’s attacks have been resolved, add up the damage that was inflicted. The player commanding the target unit must then allocate a number of wounds to the target unit equal to the damage that was inflicted.<br><br>Wounds are allocated one at a time to models in the target unit. You can allocate the wounds inflicted on your units as you see fit (the models do not have to be within range or visible to the attacking unit). However, if you allocate a wound to a model, you must keep on allocating wounds to that model until it is slain – a unit can never have more than one wounded model.<br><br>Some abilities allow you to make a roll to negate a wound or mortal wound allocated to a model; in this case the roll is made for each individual wound or <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Mortal-Wounds">mortal wound</a> as it is allocated to the model in question. If the wound or mortal wound is negated it has no effect on the model.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00029"><b><p>The GLOOMSPITE GITZ, <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WIZARDS">WIZARD</a> and HERO keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Fungoid-Cave-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Fungoid Cave-Shaman</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Madcap-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Madcap Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skragrott-the-Loonking" style="color:#101010">Skragrott, the Loonking</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Zarbag" style="color:#101010">Zarbag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  class="clFl sForgeWorld" style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Forge World: Monstrous Arcanum (2th edition)" src="/aos/img/expansions/FW_AoS_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Troggoth-Hag" style="color:#101010">Troggoth Hag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00030"><div class="tooltip_header">Running</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Running"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
When you pick a unit to make a normal move, you can declare that it will run. Make a run roll for the unit by rolling a dice. Add the result of the run roll to the Move characteristic of all models in the unit for that <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#MOVEMENT-PHASE">movement phase</a>. The unit can then move up to that distance in inches. Models in a unit that runs can’t <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#SHOOTING-PHASE">shoot</a> or <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#CHARGE-PHASE">charge</a> later in the same turn.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00031"><b><p>The SPIDERFANG and <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WIZARDS">WIZARD</a> keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00032"><b><p>The SPIDERFANG and MONSTER keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Arachnarok-Spider-with-Flinger" style="color:#101010">Arachnarok Spider with Flinger</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Arachnarok-Spider-with-Spiderfang-Warparty" style="color:#101010">Arachnarok Spider with Spiderfang Warparty</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skitterstrand-Arachnarok" style="color:#101010">Skitterstrand Arachnarok</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00033"><b><p>The <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/#Jaws-of-Mork-Allegiance-Abilities">JAWS OF MORK</a> and MANGLER SQUIGS keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Mangler-Squigs" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Mangler Squigs</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Mangler-Squigs" style="color:#101010">Mangler Squigs</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00034"><div class="tooltip_header">Battleshock test, battleshock roll</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#BATTLESHOCK-PHASE"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
In the battleshock phase, both players must take battleshock tests for units from their army that have had models slain during the turn. The player whose turn it is tests first.<br><br>You must make a battleshock roll for each unit that has to take a battleshock test. To make a battleshock roll, roll a dice. Add the number of models from the unit that have been slain this turn to the dice roll, and add 1 to the unit’s Bravery characteristic for every 10 models that are in the unit when the test is taken.<br><br>If the modified battleshock roll is greater than the unit’s modified Bravery characteristic, the battleshock test has been failed. If the test is failed, for each point by which the modified roll exceeds the unit’s modified Bravery characteristic, one model in that unit must flee. You decide which of the models from your units flee – remove them from play and count them as having been slain.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00035"><b><p>The <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/#Jaws-of-Mork-Allegiance-Abilities">JAWS OF MORK</a> and HERO keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Dankhold-Troggboss" style="color:#101010">Dankhold Troggboss</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Fungoid-Cave-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Fungoid Cave-Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss" style="color:#101010">Loonboss</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Giant-Cave-Squig" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Giant Cave Squig</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-with-Giant-Cave-Squig" style="color:#101010">Loonboss with Giant Cave Squig</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Madcap-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Madcap Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Mollog" style="color:#101010">Mollog</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Scuttleboss-on-Gigantic-Spider" style="color:#101010">Scuttleboss on Gigantic Spider</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skragrott-the-Loonking" style="color:#101010">Skragrott, the Loonking</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Zarbag" style="color:#101010">Zarbag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Mangler-Squigs" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Mangler Squigs</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  class="clFl sForgeWorld" style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Forge World: Monstrous Arcanum (2th edition)" src="/aos/img/expansions/FW_AoS_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Troggoth-Hag" style="color:#101010">Troggoth Hag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00036"><b><p>The GLOOMSPITE GITZ and HERO keywords are used in following Gloomspite Gitz warscrolls:</p></b><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Dankhold-Troggboss" style="color:#101010">Dankhold Troggboss</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Fungoid-Cave-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Fungoid Cave-Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss" style="color:#101010">Loonboss</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Giant-Cave-Squig" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Giant Cave Squig</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-with-Giant-Cave-Squig" style="color:#101010">Loonboss with Giant Cave Squig</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Madcap-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Madcap Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Mollog" style="color:#101010">Mollog</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Scuttleboss-on-Gigantic-Spider" style="color:#101010">Scuttleboss on Gigantic Spider</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Skragrott-the-Loonking" style="color:#101010">Skragrott, the Loonking</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Zarbag" style="color:#101010">Zarbag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div><div style="clear:both; margin-bottom:8px;"><div class="BatRole">Leader, Behemoth</div><div class="BreakInsideAvoid"><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Loonboss-on-Mangler-Squigs" style="color:#101010">Loonboss on Mangler Squigs</a></div></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Webspinner-Shaman-on-Arachnarok-Spider" style="color:#101010">Webspinner Shaman on Arachnarok Spider</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div  class="clFl sForgeWorld" style="padding: 1px 10px 1px 15px"><span style="color:#101010">•&nbsp;</span><img class="tooltip logo2" title="Expansion. Forge World: Monstrous Arcanum (2th edition)" src="/aos/img/expansions/FW_AoS_logo2.png"><a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/factions/gloomspite-gitz/Troggoth-Hag" style="color:#101010">Troggoth Hag</a></div><div style="clear:both"></div></div></span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00037"><div class="tooltip_header">Normal Moves</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Normal-Moves"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Moves made in the movement phase are referred to as normal moves, to differentiate them from charge moves (made in the <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#CHARGE-PHASE">charge phase</a>) and <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Piling-In">pile-in</a> moves (made in the <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#COMBAT-PHASE">combat phase</a>). A model making a normal move can move a distance in inches equal to or less than the Move characteristic shown on its <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#WARSCROLLS-1">warscroll</a>.
</span></div><div class="tooltip_templates"><span id="tooltip_content00038"><div class="tooltip_header">Reserves</div><a href="/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Reserves"><div class="tooltip_link"></div></a><div style="clear:both"></div>
Reserves are <a href="http://wahapedia.ru/aos/the-rules/the-core-rules#Units">units</a> that are part of your army, but which have an ability that allows you to set them up in a location other than on the battlefield and deploy them later once the battle has begun. Setting up a reserve unit is not considered a move for the unit, but it may restrict a unit’s ability to move in the same turn. Any reserves that have not been set up when the battle ends are treated as if they had been slain when you are working out which side won the battle.
